{{Top|leg}}
'''''Action Tidings''''' was the name of a [[Media/Legends|media]] news outlet broadcast from a [[Action Tidings studio|studio]] in the [[Action Tidings Tower|''Action Tidings'' Tower]] in the [[Ugnaught/Legends|Ugnaught]] city of [[Ugnorgrad/Legends|Ugnorgrad]], one [[Kilometer/Legends|kilometer]] below [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]]. Ugnaught reporters would broadcast live feeds of daily events from within the confines of their [[floatboat]] caravans, held aloft by large bladders filled with [[Tibanna/Legends|tibanna]] gas. [[3 ABY/Legends|Three years]] after the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], an ''Action Tidings'' news anchor named [[Ars Fivvle]] and his cameraman, [[Pordimer|Pordy]], recorded the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] coup against the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Administrator/Legends|administrator]] of Cloud City, [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Hugo Treece]].

{{Company-stub}}

The episode ''[[Ugnaughts' Progress]]'' was the last ''Action Tidings'' episode by Ars Fivvle, including a look back at 50 [[Standard year/Legends|years]] of past broadcast footage.<ref name="Wizards">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20040930bespinmain|text=Bespin: Action Tidings|int=Bespin: Action Tidings}}</ref>

